{
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Validate Every LLM Call",
  "description": "Every LLM call must have retry, JSON stripping, sleep\n",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "agents/*.py"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "When any agent file is saved, find every call to \nmodel.generate_content(). For each one verify ALL of \nthese exist:\n1. Wrapped in try/except with for attempt in range(2)\n2. response.text checked not empty before parsing\n3. re.sub strips markdown: \n   re.sub(r'```json\\s*', '', text)\n   re.sub(r'```\\s*', '', text)\n4. json.loads() called on cleaned text\n5. On JSONDecodeError attempt 0: sleep then append \n   \"RETURN ONLY RAW JSON. NO TEXT BEFORE OR AFTER.\" \n   to prompt\n6. Token usage logged:\n   print(f\"[AgentName] Tokens: {response.usage_metadata}\")\n7. time.sleep(RATE_LIMIT_SLEEP) before call if another \n   LLM call precedes it in same function\nIf any missing, add them. Never change business logic."
  }
}